The paper involves the integration of deep neural networks into a heuristic tree search procedure for solving optimization problems. This suggests that it could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of data analysis to customize heuristics could also place it under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the application of the approach to the container pre-marshalling problem could suggest a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) in terms of analyzing and optimizing the arrangement of containers.
